digitalocean:index/kubernetesNodePool:Ku.description:
Provides a DigitalOcean Kubernetes node pool resource. While the default node pool must be defined in the `digitalocean.KubernetesCluster` resource, this resource can be used to add additional ones to a cluster.

{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage
{{% example %}}
### Basic Example

```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as digitalocean from "@pulumi/digitalocean";

const foo = new digitalocean.KubernetesCluster("foo", {
    region: "nyc1",
    version: "1.22.8-do.1",
    nodePool: {
        name: "front-end-pool",
        size: "s-2vcpu-2gb",
        nodeCount: 3,
    },
});
const bar = new digitalocean.KubernetesNodePool("bar", {
    clusterId: foo.id,
    size: "c-2",
    nodeCount: 2,
    tags: ["backend"],
    labels: {
        service: "backend",
        priority: "high",
    },
    taints: [{
        key: "workloadKind",
        value: "database",
        effect: "NoSchedule",
    }],
});
```
